the supreme court has reduced the governments 
protection against lawsuits by victims of defective federally 
licensed vaccines but some authorities say the rulings impact may 
be limited 
the justices ruled unanimously monday that the parents of kevan 
berkovitz a pennsylvania boy crippled by polio may sue the 
government 
