percent he said i do not know whether we will be able to 
conclude such a treaty this year but we will make our best effort 
it is the united states top arms control priority he added 
shultzs speech underlined past accomplishments including the 
newly ratified ussoviet treaty to destroy intermediaterange 
nuclear missiles and the verification procedures that go with it 
last week soviet foreign minister eduard a shevardnadze used a 
speech to the conference to call on the united states to take on 
future disarmament challenges 
he proposed abolishing all nuclear weapons by the year 2000 an 
immediate mutual ban on nuclear tests and an immediate cut of 
500000 troops each from the warsaw pact and nato 
shultz replied that the united states will concentrate on 
results which will eliminate the disparities in conventional arms 
in europe that threaten stability not schemes for equal 
reductions which will have no such effect 
nato claims the soviets have an advantage in conventional arms 
in europe 
in the speech shultz also ignored the soviet call for a mutual 
test ban 
the united states similarly failed to join a 1year unilaterial 
soviet moratorium on testing that began in august 1985 
shultz also rejected the soviet call for a un arms reduction 
verification agency to coordinate and monitor disarmament pacts 
some tasks such as work to reduce nuclear arsenals must be 
strictly bilateral in negotiation verification and 
implementation 
but others shultz said above all the negotiations to 
ban chemical weapons and the need to control nuclear proliferation 
are global problems 
shultz offered no specific proposals on those problems 
ballistic missile proliferation is a new and urgent 
challenge particularly in the middle east said shultz his 
advice to iran and iraq was to exercise mutual restraint and 
not buy or launch such missiles 
shultz urged nations attending the conference on disarmament to 
apply themselves to a global ban on chemical weapons which are 
easily made in fertilizer and pesticide factories but did not 
suggest any solutions 
the potential spread of nuclear weapons to other countries 
especially in south asia is a central topic in the uns session 
on disarmament and shultz urged rivals pakistan and india to work 
on the problem 
earlier in the day pakistan offered to sign the nuclear 
nonproliferation treaty if india does so simultaneously 
later this week delegates to the 159member general assembly 
will begin drafting resolutions on chemical nuclear conventional 
and spacebased weapons for this third special session on 
disarmament in 10 years 
the session scheduled to end june 25 has been sharply divided 
diplomatic observers said it will be difficult to draft a final 
document 
the united states and western allies have called for pragmatic 
steps in arms control respect for nuclear deterrence a limited 
role for the united nations and recognition that bilateral arms 
talks must supersede multilateral efforts 
western diplomats also have said that conventional disarmament 
is as important as nuclear disarmament and urged poor developing 
nations that clamor for nuclear disarmament to cut their own armies 
and avoid sweeping and utopian disarmament proposals 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

