a norwegian unit of the un peacekeeping 
force was locked in a tense confrontation with israeli troops in 
southern lebanon today un sources said 
elsewhere in southern lebanon four lebanese villagers were 
killed and four others wounded when israeli gunners shelled shiite 
moslem guerrilla hideouts in tibnin valley before dawn police said 
un sources said norwegian and israeli troops faced each other 
through the night fingers on triggers as flares illuminated the 
skies over the foothills of mount hermon 
theyre still squared off in a tense confrontation one un 
source said at midmorning he spoke on condition of anonymity 
the source said the tension developed after norwegian 
peacekeepers blocked israeli troops two days ago from setting up a 
checkpoint close to a norwegian outpost on the southern edge of 
hebbariyeh 
the village is seven miles north of israels selfdesignated 
security zone in south lebanon it has a norwegian garrison of nine 
the source said a mechanized israeli unit rolled into hebbariyeh 
monday encircled the norwegian checkpoint and warned the 
peacekeepers that they will be treated as trespassers on israeli 
territory if they leave their post 
un spokesman timur goksel confirmed the confrontation and said 
20 israeli troops in two armored personnel carriers and a bulldozer 
were surrounding the norwegian position 
goksel said 50 other norwegian troops were dispatched to 
hebbariyeh to help the encircled position they removed barbedwire 
barricades set by the israelis around the checkpoint he said 
norway has an 881strong battalion in the un interim force in 
lebanon unifil comprises 5800 troops drawn from nine nations 
unifil deployed in south lebanon in 1978 to serve as a buffer 
between palestinian guerrillas and israels northern border its 
area overlaps with the security zone israel carved out in south 
lebanon in 1985 
unifil is against any israeli position to be set up in unifil 
area because it will cause a lot of tension goksel said 
he said contacts were under way to ease the hebbariyeh tension 
which he said was still running high this morning 
police said the tibnin valley shelling apparently was prompted 
by reports in the security zone of abnormal guerrilla activity in 
the area 
thirty mortar rounds crashed in and around tibnin overnight all 
eight casualties were civilians police said 
