of the us military liaison mission allowed under the terms of a 
1947 treaty to keep tabs on soviet military activities inside east 
germany 
on the day he died nicholson and a driver sgt jessie g 
schatz were trying to observe a soviet tank shed according to the 
us account nicholson was close to but not in a restricted 
area when a soviet sentry suddenly opened fire without warning 
the pentagon has charged that schatz was directly prevented from 
going to the wounded man with his first aid kit and that the major 
was left to die without medical attention the defense department 
also noted angrily at the time that soviet military inspectors 
working inside west germany had never been threatened with being 
shot 
