the house appropriations committee voted 
tuesday to let the next president decide whether to fund 
construction of a space station 
under the bill approved by the committee 387 million would be 
available for research and development between oct 1 when the 
next fiscal year begins and april 15 when the next president 
would have to decide whether to continue with the space station 
another 654 million would be held in an account and should 
the president decide not to proceed further those funds would be 
used to shut down the program 
additionally 450 million would be held through april 15 if 
the new president decided to continue with the program the money 
would go to the space station if he decided against the space 
station 150 million would be transferred to space flight control 
and data communications at the national aeronautics and space 
administration the remaining 300 million would be rescinded 
under the bill the new president would have to let congress 
know between feb 1 and april 15 of his intentions to continue with 
the space station 
if its democrat michael dukakis it could be the end of the 
space station said rep tom delay rtexas the guy is a 
northern liberal this is set up to pit domestic spending against 
defense spending 
delay whose houstonarea district borders johnson space center 
said about half of the station would be built in houston 
