white house chief of staff howard h baker on 
tuesday became the latest reagan administration official to 
announce his resignation before the presidents term expires in 
january 
here is how the cabinet and top adminstration posts have changed 
since president reagan took office in 1981 
secretary of defense frank c carlucci was sworn in nov 23 
1987 replacing caspar w weinberger who had held the post since 
january 1981 
national security adviser colin powell succeeded carlucci 
carlucci had been named to the post by reagan on dec 2 1986 
replacing john m poindexter who resigned in the wake of the 
irancontra affair poindexter had taken over from robert c 
mcfarlane in december 1985 mcfarlane had succeeded william p 
clark in november 1983 clark had replaced richard v allen in 1982 
secretary of state george p shultz replaced alexander m haig 
jr in 1982 after haig resigned 
secretary of the treasury james a baker iii became treasury 
secretary in 1985 replacing donald regan who became white house 
chief of staff the two traded jobs 
justice department attorney general edwin meese iii who served 
as white house counselor during reagans first term replaced 
william french smith at the justice department feb 25 1985 
secretary of the interior donald p hodel took office in 
february 1985 replacing william p clark who resigned clark had 
taken over from james g watt who quit in october 1983 and left 
office the next month 
secretary of agriculture richard e lyng was sworn into office 
in march 1986 taking the place of john r block 
secretary of commerce c william verity jr was sworn into 
office oct 19 1987 succeeding malcolm baldrige who died july 25 
from injuries suffered when a horse he was riding fell on him 
secretary of labor ann dore mclaughlin was sworn into office on 
dec 17 1987 replacing william e brock who left to join bob 
doles unsuccessful campaign for the republican presidential 
nomination brock had held the office since april 1985 replacing 
raymond j donovan 
secretary of health and human services otis r bowen was sworn 
into office in december 1985 taking over from margaret m heckler 
who became ambassador to ireland mrs heckler had replaced richard 
s schweiker who resigned in january 1983 
secretary of transportation james h burnley iv was sworn into 
office dec 3 1987 replacing elizabeth hanford dole who resigned 
to join her husbands presidential campaign mrs dole had replaced 
drew lewis who quit in december 1982 
secretary of housing and urban development samuel r pierce 
jr reagans original hud secretary was sworn into office jan 
23 1981 
secretary of energy john s herrington was sworn into office in 
february 1985 replacing donald p hodel who became secretary of 
the interior hodel had taken over at the energy department after 
james b edwards resigned in november 1982 
