not told it was coming from wolfson and not from a bank 
the loan was hidden on a campaign financial report as part of a 
fabricated 465000 lump sum listed as a contribution from 
mecham cudahy said he also pointed to a letter in which mecham 
promised wolfson the loan would remain confidential 
scott contended that the loan was properly reported as part of 
the 465000 lump sum because mecham was responsible for its 
repayment 
mecham was charged with six felony counts of perjury willful 
concealment and filing false documents and faced up to 22 years in 
prison if convicted 
willard mecham who was his brothers 1986 campaign treasurer 
faced three similar counts and up to 9 years in prison if 
convicted 
mecham a republican took office in january 1987 and was 
removed april 4 when the state senate convicted him of two 
