<TEXT>
the government is trying to tame the wide 
swings in the monthly us trade deficit changes which in the past 
have sent stock prices plunging but analysts are not sure the 
effortwill be a success 
financial markets were braced for more bad news today with 
release of the trade deficit for april in advance of the report 
many economists were predicting the deficit could widen to around 
123 billion compared to a march deficit of 119 billion 
the last time the trade deficit widened when the february 
figure was reported the dollar came under intense selling pressure 
worldwide and the dow jones industrial average fell by 101 points 
its fifthworst loss ever 
analysts didnt expect such a dramatic reaction to this report 
mainly because financial markets already were expecting the april 
deficit to be higher however if it came in much higher than the 
expected 123 billion it had the potential to set off alarms in 
financial markets 
for the first time in two years the government has begun 
seasonally adjusting the monthly deficit figures to take into 
account normal seasonal changes in shipping patterns 
most government statistics are adjusted to factor out 
fluctuations which occur on a seasonal basis such as the normal 
rise in retail sales right before christmas 
the government was forced to abandon seasonal adjustments of the 
trade figures in december 1985 because of lags in gathering the 
data those problems have since been corrected and seasonal 
adjustments are being reintroduced 
by adjusting for normal seasonal swings the government hopes to 
make the trade series less erratic and therefore ease the jolt 
financial markets sometimes receive 
a string of bad monthly trade figures was blamed for adding to 
the pessimistic mood right before last octobers stock market crash 
and there have been other periodic jolts including the big drop in 
the stock market after the february deficit figure was released 
but allen sinai chief economist for the boston co said he did 
not believe the seasonal adjustments will do much to smooth out the 
monthly swings because of the erratic nature of trade shipments 
when any single month can be affected by a number of factors 
in fact one reason analysts were looking for a wider deficit 
figure in april was the absence of gold shipments to taiwan in 
march the taiwan government purchased over 700 million in gold as 
a way of lowering its trade surplus with the united states which 
has been pressuring taiwan to do more to open up its country to 
american goods 
even with erratic monthtomonth swings economists are 
optimistic that the overall trade deficit which hit a record 
1703 billion is finally headed lower 
the trade deficit is slowly turning and that should be the 
story for the rest of the year sinai said 
a recent survey by the national association of business 
economists showed they expect the trade defict to decline to around 
150 billion this year and 125 billion in 1989 
</TEXT>
