the dollar leaped in value against most major 
foreign currencies tuesday in reaction to a report that the us 
merchandise trade deficit narrowed in april to a 
betterthanexpected 989 billion 
gold prices finished mixed after initially being knocked down by 
the trade news republic national bank of new york said gold was 
bid at 45015 a troy ounce as of 4 pm edt up from 44970 late 
monday 
in its strongest move in months the dollar climbed 16 percent 
against the west german mark although west germanys central bank 
sold dollars in an attempt to stem the us currencys rise 
traders said 
the dollar also rose 17 percent against the british pound and 
by slightly less against other european currencies and the japanese 
yen it slipped against the canadian dollar in part because a 
strong bond rally lowered yields on us securities in comparison 
to canadian securities 
traders said there were no confirmed reports of dollar selling 
by central banks other than west germanys 
