japans mazda motor corp will combine its two 
us sales and importing companies into one july 1 eliminating 70 
jobs at one of the companies headquarters in jacksonville fla 
mazda is combining mazda motors of america central and mazda 
motors of america east into mazda motor of america inc about 20 of 
the 330 workers at the mazda east headquarters will be laid off by 
the end of june yoshinori taura president of the new irvine 
califbased company said tuesday 
in the next three to six months 45 to 50 other jacksonville 
workers will be laid off but those workers were given bonuses to 
stay through the transition and all 70 will be assisted in finding 
jobs taura said 
i feel very sorry for those workers it is not our desire to 
have to ask them to leave we will help them taura said adding 
that the consolidation would improve mazdas efficiency in the us 
market 
we believe the improved efficiency and services that will 
result from this reorganization of our us marketing activity will 
be reflected in an enriched product line one which more closely 
reflects the needs and desires of our customers here taura said 
the use of two sales companies by a foreign company in the 
united states was unique to mazda mazda central which included 31 
states and mazda east which included 18 were formed 11 years 
ago when mazda was suffering financially a company that imported 
into hawaii also will be folded into the new company 
