<TEXT>
the ruling liberal democratic party approved a 
blueprint for sweeping reform of the national tax system on 
tuesday and pegged a controversial consumer sales tax at 3 
percent party officials said 
the ldps tax system research council completed the final plan 
that could pave the way for the first major overhaul of japans 
postwar tax system 
the ldp draft includes some 448 billion in tax cuts corporate 
and personal income tax rates as well as inheritance levies will be 
cut in the new tax plan which ldp officials say they hope to 
implement by april 1989 
it took six months for us only to agree on the sales tax 
rate said sadanori yamanaka the legislator who heads the 
council now the party must be firmly united under the new plan 
to overcome the opposition parties attempt to block the bill 
the new tax plan caps long and fiercelydebated sessions 
regarding the amount of tax reductions and the level of sales taxes 
among ruling party members and finance ministry officials 
but it also is expected to come under hot debate from opposition 
parties in the upcoming session of the diet the japanese 
parliament 
the new plan finalized tuesday marks the third attempt by the 
government and ruling party to introduce an indirect tax following 
others in 1979 and 1987 
last year thenprime minister yasuhiro nakasone suffered a 
serious political setback when his party was defeated in local 
elections over the sales tax issue 
shintaro abe ldp secretary general said after unveiling the 
new tax plan that the party still faced the task of garnering wide 
support for the reform package 
we have just completed the first stage he said the next 
steps are going to be the real challenge but i think there is a 
consensus within the party 
opposition party leaders denounced the ruling partys decision 
to push forward with the oncedefeated tax reform plan 
it is a serious challenge to the people of our country said 
shizuo yamaguchi secretary general of the japan socialist party 
the largest opposition party the ldp must dissolve the diet and 
let the people decide on the issue 
satsuki eda chairman of the social democratic alliance said 
i am determined to cooperate with other opposition parties to 
block the passage of the new tax law in the diet by all means 
the finance ministry which had sought a 5 percent sales tax 
also welcomed the new tax system as a boost to the domestic economy 
the new tax system is expected to lift the gross national 
product by 01 percent said a finance ministry official as a 
result the japanese economy will be vitalized and expanded 
domestic demand will draw more imports 
finance ministry officials have argued that revenue from a 3 
percent sales tax would total only about 40 billion to 43 
billion short of the amount slated in tax cuts 
the ministry has said it hopes to eliminate budget 
deficitcovering bond issues by fiscal 1990 but may have to revise 
its target if the new ldp plan is passed 
an ldp official said the tax plan will be presented to the diet 
in july for passage by next fall 
</TEXT>
